-- Belgian Government Raises 2010 Inflation Outlook to 2.2%, Keeps 2011 at 2%
-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 2010-11-03T10:51:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/belgian-government-raises-2010-inflation-outlook-to-2-2-keeps-2011-at-2-.html
Belgium’s federal planning bureau
raised its forecast for the average increase in 2010 consumer
prices to 2.2 percent from 2.1 percent, according to a statement
posted on the government agency’s Web site.  Belgium’s planning bureau maintained its prediction for
average inflation of 2 percent next year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Martens at 
